<DOC><DOCNO> AP880423-0144 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-04-23-88 2050EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r a AM-People SUB a0579 04-23 0142</FIRST><SECOND>AM-People, SUB, a0579,0145</SECOND><NOTE>Eds: SUBS 1st item to CORRECT day in 3rd graf to Thursday, stedWednesday</NOTE><DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   To drawn-out chants of ``Bruuuuce Bruuuuce,''rock music idol Bruce Springsteen opened a five-night concertseries at the Los Angeles Sports Arena, his first in the city in 2{years.   Friday night's performance before a crowd of 15,000 was slightlymore intimate than Springsteen's ``Born in the USA Tour''performances at the nearby Los Angeles Memorial Coliseum in 1985.More than 80,000 people jammed the Coliseum for each of those shows.   The 22-city ``Tunnel of Love'' tour, featuring Springsteen,known as ``the Boss'' to his fans, and his E Street Band continuesin Los Angeles through Thursday.   ``He makes you into a leader,'' said fan Adam Schellin, 19, ofsuburban Simi Valley. ``He pulls me up when I'm down.''</TEXT></DOC>